## Quick start

```bash
curl -fsSL creation.dev/install | bash
creation serve          # web dashboard at http://127.0.0.1:8787
creation tui            # terminal UI (run serve in another tab)
```

The installer adds a `creation` command (via `pipx`, or an isolated env it manages for you) — **no repo clone, no source on disk.** The UI ships inside the package. If you already have `pipx`, `pipx install git+https://github.com/arjunkshah/creation.git` does the same thing.

Already installed? Update in place — no reinstall:

```bash
creation update
```

Developing on Creation? Get the source instead:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/arjunkshah/creation.git && cd creation
./bootstrap.sh && source .venv/bin/activate && creation serve
```

Open [http://127.0.0.1:8787](http://127.0.0.1:8787) → onboard → describe your idea → **Send**.

```bash
creation run --idea "CLI that syncs Linear to markdown" --agent codex   # headless + live progress
creation run --idea "Add OAuth login" --workdir ~/code/my-app           # build in place on an existing repo
creation run --verbose                                                 # stream agent output
creation run --demo                                                    # pipeline without live keys
creation doctor                                                        # verify keys, Composio, agents
```

---

## Run on an existing repo

Creation isn't greenfield-only — point it at **any directory** and it builds *in place* instead of scaffolding from scratch:

```bash
creation run --workdir ~/code/my-app --idea "Add OAuth login and a settings page"
creation run -C .         --idea "Fix the failing auth tests"   # -C is shorthand for --workdir
```

In the **dashboard**, click **Choose folder** under the prompt and pick the repo (leave it on **Default** for a fresh build under `~/.creation`).

When the target directory already contains code, Creation:

- **Detects the existing codebase** and tells the agent to read it and modify in place — no new scaffold, no overwriting unrelated files.
- **Skips template scaffolding** so your files are never clobbered (templates only seed empty workdirs).
- **Never deletes your repo** — Creation's project cleanup only removes folders it manages under `~/.creation/projects`.

Phrase the idea as a change request ("Add…", "Fix…", "Refactor…"). Creation creates a safe `creation/<slug>` branch, reuses your GitHub remote, and plans **surgical edits** instead of a greenfield MVP. Commit or branch first so each turn's push/PR has a clean baseline.

---

## Launch marketing (Resend + Ayrshare)

When a build completes, Creation can auto-run a **launch campaign**:

| Channel | Provider | What it does |
|---------|----------|--------------|
| **Email** | [Resend](https://resend.com) | Launch email to your list or segment |
| **Social + video** | [Ayrshare](https://ayrshare.com) | One API call → X, LinkedIn, Instagram, TikTok, YouTube, Threads, Reddit, … |

In **Settings → Launch marketing**:

1. Enable **Marketing on ship**
2. **Resend** — API key + From address + recipients (or segment ID)
3. **Ayrshare** — API key + platforms (`twitter,linkedin,instagram` or `all`)
4. Optional **Media URL** — HTTPS video/image for Reels/TikTok/YouTube posts

Connect your social accounts once in the [Ayrshare dashboard](https://app.ayrshare.com). Gmail (Composio) still handles *your* build notifications; this handles *audience* launch.

